This paper is about human gender recognition in computer vision, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the challenges faced in recognizing gender from whole body images and gait sequences, which falls under the sub-category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of different methods, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper also mentions datasets used for gender recognition, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM).
